&lt;h3&gt;&lt;br&gt;The role:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive - iIngredients Club you&amp;nbsp; will be a key member of our newly established Ingredients Club team. This team represents a new business line designed to extend the benefits of CookUnity’s core meal subscription business into the broader restaurant industry. Our goal is to leverage the strong supplier relationships, cost efficiencies, and operational expertise built through CookUnity&#39;s meal subscription platform to offer restaurants a powerful supply chain solution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play a critical role in driving the growth of this new business line by forming strategic partnerships with restaurants and food service businesses. Your focus will be on helping these businesses reduce food costs, optimize their supply chain, and improve reliability through our tailored offerings. This is a unique opportunity to be part of a new, high-growth area within a well-established company, contributing to both the success of our partners and the expansion of CookUnity’s overall business model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Growth:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage the full sales cycle, from prospecting and lead qualification through closing deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt; Build, expand, and maintain strong relationships with restaurant groups, food service businesses, and suppliers.

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About CookUnity:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Food has lost its soul to modern convenience. And with it, it has lost the power to nourish, inspire, and connect us. So in 2018, CookUnity was founded as the first-of-its-kind platform that connects the world with the source of truly great food: chefs. Today, CookUnity delivers 50 million meals a year from the industry’s best chefs to homes all over the country. Fresh. Ready-to-eat. And crafted with the passion that nourishes body and soul.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Unwilling to stop there, CookUnity is expanding beyond delivery to become an ever-innovating marketplace focused on our singular mission: &lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;empower Chefs to nourish the world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;If that mission has you hungry in more ways than one, you’ve found the right job posting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About the Team:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OffMenu is a new product from Cookin (a CookUnity company) that helps top local restaurants launch and grow their own subscription programs, turning their biggest fans into recurring members. We’re in an early pilot stage with a small group of Toronto restaurants and are now hiring our first sales hire to help us bring more great merchants onto the platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The role:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our first Account Executive (Restaurants Partnership), you will own the top and middle of the funnel: researching ideal restaurant partners, reaching out, running intro conversations, and supporting them through onboarding onto OffMenu. You’ll combine personable, in‑person and remote relationship‑building with heavy use of AI tools to research, personalize outreach, and keep yourself highly productive. This is an entry‑level role ideal for someone hungry, coachable, and excited about restaurants, tech, and AI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and prioritize target restaurants that match OffMenu’s ideal partner profile (strong regular base, hero dishes, operationally solid).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools (chatbots, research assistants, email‑drafting tools, simple lead‑scoring sheets) to research prospects, prepare outreach, and log notes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run outbound outreach (email, Instagram/DMs, phone, in‑person drop‑bys, events) to book meetings with restaurant owners and operators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct discovery calls: understand each restaurant’s concept, regulars, delivery setup, and whether a subscription makes sense for them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the OffMenu product/ops team to move qualified prospects through a structured onboarding process (from verbal “yes” through contract and launch).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clean pipeline tracking in our CRM/spreadsheet, using AI where helpful to summarize calls and organize data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect qualitative feedback from merchants about their pains, expectations, and experience, and feed that back into product and onboarding improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experiment with new outreach scripts, positioning, and channels and help us refine our go‑to‑market playbook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll be building process, not stepping into a mature playbook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading all sales activities for food merchants across Canada &amp;amp; US.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must‑have qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of experience in sales, partnerships, community, hospitali

