&lt;h3&gt;The role:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CookUnity is seeking an experienced and highly strategic Director, Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality Assurance to lead and scale food safety excellence across our NYC operations. This role is critical to enabling CookUnity’s rapid growth and marketplace expansion by building best-in-class, data-driven food safety systems that protect our customers, strengthen brand trust, and support operational innovation at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CookUnity operates at the intersection of culinary innovation, direct-to-consumer distribution, and multi-site ready-to-eat production, requiring a leader who can balance speed of growth with disciplined control of core risks such as sanitation, cold chain integrity, supplier governance, and regulatory alignment across jurisdictions. This role offers the rare opportunity to build foundational programs, influence product and operational design, and embed food safety as a strategic enabler of growth as CookUnity expands its geographic footprint, SKU complexity, and marketplace ecosystem. The Director will partner cross-functionally to translate emerging risks into pragmatic controls that protect consumers, strengthen brand trust, and support the company’s trajectory toward category leadership and potential public market readiness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the site Food Safety leader, this role owns the end-to-end food safety strategy and execution for one of CookUnity’s most complex markets. Reporting into the VP, Food Safety &amp;amp; Quality Assurance, this leader will act as a key thought partner across Operations, Culinary, Supply Chain, and Regulatory teams—ensuring food safety is deeply embedded into how we design, build, and scale our production systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate operates at both a strategic and systems level, while remaining close enough to execution to drive impact on the ground. They bring strong leadership presence, the ability to influence at all levels, and a track record of building scalable programs in high-growth environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive the end-to-end food safety strategy for NYC operations, aligning with company-wide growth, marketplace expansion, and operational excellence g

